title: application-gateway-configure-ssl-policy-powershell
content:
# Configure TLS policy using PowerShell

This article provides instructions on how to configure TLS Policy on Azure Application Gateway using PowerShell. It includes information on selecting predefined policies or creating a custom TLS policy based on specific requirements.

**NOTE:** This document discusses configuration through the Azure Portal. Please _always_ use infrastructure-as-code (IaC) for production environments and deploy through Azure DevOps pipelines.

## Get available TLS options

To get a list of available TLS options, you can use the `Get-AzApplicationGatewayAvailableSslOptions` cmdlet. This will provide information on predefined policies, cipher suites, and protocol versions that can be configured. It is important to note that the default TLS policy is set to "AppGwSslPolicy20220101" for API versions 2023-02-01 or higher.

## List pre-defined TLS policies

Azure Application Gateway offers multiple pre-defined policies that can be used. You can retrieve these policies using the `Get-AzApplicationGatewaySslPredefinedPolicy` cmdlet. Each policy has different protocol versions and cipher suites enabled, allowing you to choose the one that best suits your needs.

Please always use infrastructure-as-code (IaC) for production environments and deploy through Azure DevOps pipelines.
